article.headline: Texas-Pan American 87, Colo.-Colo. Springs 78
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Nick Weiermiller scored 19 points and had eight assists to lead Texas-Pan American to a 87-78 win over the University of Colorado-Colorado Springs on Sunday. The win came in the second round of the Reggie Minton Air Force Classic hosted by the Air Force Academy. Emmanuel Jones scored 16 points for the Broncs. P.J. Turner added 14 and Ben Smith had 11. Nick Weaver led Colorado-Colorado Springs with 15 points, including two three-pointers. Tommy Klausner scored 12 points and led his team with 10 rebounds. Texas-Pan American lost 75-70 to Wofford in the opening round of the tournament on Saturday. Colorado-Colorado Springs lost 86-65 to Air Force.
